    • Method Detail

      • update

        public Configuration.UpdateInvocation update(ConfigurationModel model)
        Description copied from interface: Configuration
        Updates the configuration. The update is incremental. Any property in the ConfigurationModel class that is null will not be modified. Note that this update method doesn't guarantee an atomic change of all the properties. In the case of a system crash or failure, some of the properties could be left unchanged while others may be updated.

        Operation Errors:
        InvalidArgument - if one of the configuration properties is not within the proper range.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have all of the privileges described as follows:

        • Method execution requires ContentLibrary.UpdateConfiguration.

        Specified by:
        update in interface Configuration
        Parameters:
        model - The ConfigurationModel specifying the settings to update.
        Returns:
        instance of Configuration.UpdateInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described update operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
